\title{Vaex}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Use this skill for processing and analyzing large tabular datasets (billions of rows) that exceed available RAM. Vaex excels at out-of-core DataFrame operations, lazy evaluation, fast aggregations, efficient visualization of big data, and machine learning on large datasets. Apply when users need to work with large CSV/HDF5/Arrow/Parquet files, perform fast statistics on massive datasets, create visualizations of big data, or build ML pipelines that don't fit in memory.}

\subtree{
\title{Vaex}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Vaex is a high-performance Python library designed for lazy, out-of-core DataFrames to process and visualize tabular datasets that are too large to fit into RAM. Vaex can process over a billion rows per second, enabling interactive data exploration and analysis on datasets with billions of rows.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{Use Vaex when:}

\ul{
\li{Processing tabular datasets larger than available RAM (gigabytes to terabytes)}
\li{Performing fast statistical aggregations on massive datasets}
\li{Creating visualizations and heatmaps of large datasets}
\li{Building machine learning pipelines on big data}
\li{Converting between data formats (CSV, HDF5, Arrow, Parquet)}
\li{Needing lazy evaluation and virtual columns to avoid memory overhead}
\li{Working with astronomical data, financial time series, or other large-scale scientific datasets}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\p{Vaex provides six primary capability areas, each documented in detail in the references directory:}

\subtree{
\title{1. DataFrames and Data Loading}
\p{Load and create Vaex DataFrames from various sources including files (HDF5, CSV, Arrow, Parquet), pandas DataFrames, NumPy arrays, and dictionaries. Reference \code{\startverb references/core_dataframes.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Opening large files efficiently}
\li{Converting from pandas/NumPy/Arrow}
\li{Working with example datasets}
\li{Understanding DataFrame structure}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Data Processing and Manipulation}
\p{Perform filtering, create virtual columns, use expressions, and aggregate data without loading everything into memory. Reference \code{\startverb references/data_processing.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Filtering and selections}
\li{Virtual columns and expressions}
\li{Groupby operations and aggregations}
\li{String operations and datetime handling}
\li{Working with missing data}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Performance and Optimization}
\p{Leverage Vaex's lazy evaluation, caching strategies, and memory-efficient operations. Reference \code{\startverb references/performance.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Understanding lazy evaluation}
\li{Using \code{\startverb delay=True\stopverb} for batching operations}
\li{Materializing columns when needed}
\li{Caching strategies}
\li{Asynchronous operations}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Data Visualization}
\p{Create interactive visualizations of large datasets including heatmaps, histograms, and scatter plots. Reference \code{\startverb references/visualization.md\stopverb} for:}

\ul{
\li{Creating 1D and 2D plots}
\li{Heatmap visualizations}
